2	// DESCENT_BUILD_SPEC.md Part 2.1 + Part 4. Tasks D-111, D-115, D-116 (core night machine).
3	//
4	// ===== module step protocol =====
5	// The core owns Phase; a GameModule owns one circle. Two ways a module drives the night:
6	//  1. DIRECTIVES: gameState may carry reserved keys `$phase` / `$deal` (types.ts).
7	//     The core consumes + strips them after every step: `$deal` runs the 4.5 deal
8	//     ceremony (backup reserved, burn window, timing-identical), `$phase` moves the
9	//     room to INPUT / WAITING_ON / REVEAL. A core-owned REVEAL gets the full hold
10	//     machinery: DESCEND (host anytime, anyone past the 45s softcap), fire-decay
11	//     (8s of quiet past the 20s minimum hold). When the hold ends, the core calls
12	//     module.timer(ctx, CORE_REVEAL_DONE); after a deal completes, CORE_DEALT.
13	//  2. SELF-MANAGED: a module may run sub-phases inside its own gameState and schedule
14	//     its own timers (any id outside the core namespaces below). The core tracks those
15	//     schedules; a timer whose id contains ':hold:' is treated as a reveal hold that
16	//     DESCEND can fire early (host anytime, anyone past the softcap).
17	// step.done -> LADDER (5s) -> next circle or JUDGMENT. Epoch bumps on EVERY phase change.
